aa(lp133
VBut coding doesn't have to be like this.
p134
aVLet me show you about what it's like to code in Scratch.
p135
aVSo in Scratch, to code, you just snap blocks together.
p136
aVIn this case, you take a move block,
p137
aVsnap it into a stack,
p138
aVand the stacks of blocks control the behaviors
p139
aVof the different characters in your game or your story,
p140
aVin this case controlling the big fish.
p141
